DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/S0378-4266(97)00005-8
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0378426697000058
KW  - Bond market
KW  - Taxes
KW  - Arbitrage
AB  - This paper develops a geometric methodology with which to analyze the no-arbitrage condition, with special reference to tax arbitrage in government bonds. Using this methodology, it is shown that a country's bond-issuing authority might be able to painlessly avoid market equilibria which is likely to induce tax arbitrage activities. The simple bond-issuing policy which will achieve this goal is identified, and its limitations are discussed. An examination of the Canadian and Israeli bond markets shows that adopting the prescribed bond-issuing policy does not meaningfully impinge on the bond-issuing authority's ability to sell bonds.
